Use ANSI escape sequences to colorize output to a terminal. Most terminals recognize all escape sequences this library uses:

foreground color  |  bold foreground color
Black       0;30     Dark Gray     1;30
Blue        0;34     Light Blue    1;34
Green       0;32     Light Green   1;32
Cyan        0;36     Light Cyan    1;36
Red         0;31     Light Red     1;31
Purple      0;35     Light Purple  1;35
Brown       0;33     Yellow        1;33
Light Gray  0;37     White         1;37

background color
Black      40 
Red        41
Green      42
Brown      43
Blue       44
Purple     45
Cyan       46
Light Gray 47

effects
Underscore 4
Blink      5
Inverse    7
Concealed  8

to see what the colors look like and what effects are supported in your terminal, run

./test.py
